sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J119075
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: T7 RNAP produced from pLacI promoter. T7 RNAP drives expression of RFP from the pT7 promoter. T7 RNAP gene has sites for insertion of frameshift mutations.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jerrad Morton
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: T7 RNAP gene has sites for insertion of frameshift mutations.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_R0085
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The T7 promoter should only produce PoPS when the T7 polymerase is also being expressed.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Barry Canton

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: **highly** engineered mutant of red fluorescent protein from Discosoma striata (coral)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: monomeric RFP: Red Fluorescent Protein. Excitation peak: 584 nm Emission peak: 607 nm
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Campbell et al., PNAS v99 p7877 URL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
TAATAA double stop codon added (DE).
Four silent mutations made to remove three EcoRI sites and one PstI site: A28G, A76G, A349G, G337A.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J119009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: pLacI-RBS-T7RNAP with sites for oligo insertion
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: J23100 promoter and B0030 RBS upstream of T7 RNAP gene. The following restriction sites do not occur in the promoter-RBS-T7 RNAP sequence. Some of them did not occur in the original sequence and others were removed while conserving the amino acid sequence. Both the forward and reverse complement were checked for type IIs enzyme sites. EcoRI, XbaI, SpeI, PstI, AscI, AsiSI, BsaI, BsmBI, BbsI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Cody Barta
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BsmBI site (cgtctcn/ and /nnnnngagacg) before RBS and after gene coding sequence that can be used to cut out RBS-gene for placement after other promoters. Sites for AsiSI (gcgat/cgc) and AscI (gg/cgcgcc) that can be used to insert existing oligos. Sites flanking these for BsaI (ggtctcn/ and /nnnnngagacc) that can be used to insert new oligos without the need for gel purification. A site for BbsI (gaagacnn/ and /nnnnnngtcttc) that produces a sticky end complementary to the first BsaI site, for use in generating a near wild type version of the gene.
